replies.body:
I'd like to give them the benefit of the doubt with this one.

Surely they must have had a reason to remove it, nobody was picking it and it wasn't doing anything game-breaking in the current meta, so I cannot see why it had to be removed. {{summoner:10}}

EDIT: unclear

All summoners spells should stay there regardless. It's a thing to want the game balanced higher level. It's another to remove the fun of custom games / half troll builds

MS {{champion:120}} 
Zombie {{champion:30}} 
Everywhere{{champion:98}} and {{champion:80}} and {{champion:421}} 
Incoming Chiming Bard

MS Hecarim got nerfed soon after his release, but is still played for fun in normals. Zombie Karthus is viable if you want to carry some games and still laugh at your death counter.

Revive is still a thing if you want to survive a late game base after an ace. Removing a summoner spell is just plain out removing diversity. It's not because most players consider it a troll summoner spell that it is.

@Meddler 
@Riot
@Ghostcrawler
@Sotere
@Morello
@Anyone...

Executioner's Calling was an absolutely fabulous item. Every time I would get it when playing against Mundo, Hecarim, Lee, etc.
The fact is, people need to stop looking at lcs players and trying to model themselves exactly after them. Like it's okay to pick up sometips and learn, but be fucking original. You go out of meta in champion select and get called a noob and a troll and then when you do successfully, no one fucking acknowledges you. An lcs player goes out of meta in select and everyone raises an eyebrow, then when they do successfully, they get praised and it's 'new meta'. I'm really getting sick and tired of the stigma. I've played Katarina since S2 and I can say that I can play her top and mid quite well. I've won against most Jax and Xin Zhao picks and that's a pretty good feat if I do say so myself. I mained adc in S4 but it got too tiring to play when they removed executioner's which further confirmed "status builds" on adcs like you're only supposed to build one way. Nobody fucking used Revive? Not sure if you took a survey of every single League player and was able to draw that conclusion. Just because it was an unpopular spell, doesn't mean that should be the justification of a removal. And I care because I don't want them to add more items and make the game more diverse, just to shrink it again so we can all feel like fucking pro players.
Step your pussy game up, honey.{{champion:51}}
